%N A398013 Decimal expansion of -Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * d(k^2) * log(k) / k^2, where lambda is Liouville's function (A008836), and d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%H A398013 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 380, Corollary 2.8.
%F A398013 Equals (2*Pi^2/75) * (log(2*Pi) + gamma + 36*log(A) + 480*log(A_3)), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%e A398013 0.382994320213487041146500759983045806878397629984631...
%t A398013 RealDigits[(2*Pi^2/75) * (Log[2*Pi] + EulerGamma + 36*Log[Glaisher] - 480*Zeta'[-3] - 22/3), 10, 120][[1]]
